snippet.description: Here you'll find our current five overall-favorite car stereos, but check in regularly for updates a

snippet.title: Zubie Connected Car Service
snippet.description: The Zubie Connected Car Service keeps good track of the family car and can help people be better drivers, but the lack of fuel economy information is a big miss.

snippet.title: Jet Car Stunts 2
snippet.description: Jet Car Stunts 2 improves on almost every aspect of the original game, and the free-to-play pricing model is just about as good as it gets, but download only if you're up for a serious challenge.

snippet.title: Steelie Car Mount Kit
snippet.description: The Steelie phone mount kit consists of a steel ball and a magnetic grommet, which together make for a secure car-mounting system.

snippet.title: iOmounts iOauto Car Mount
snippet.description: iOmounts' magnet-based iOauto makes mounting a phone in your car easy, but it is an ugly-looking thing, and requires a bright, silver disc on the back of your phone.

snippet.title: NKMOS Ultima In-Car Universal Smartphone Holder
snippet.description: This solidly constructed aluminum smartphone holder has a nice finish, but a short mounting arm means difficult in-car positioning.

snippet.title: Audiovox Car Connection
snippet.description: The Audiovox Car Connection's main benefit is letting parents keep track of their children's driving behavior for a relatively low per-month price.

snippet.title: Shuttle bus protest hits Microsoft in Seattle
snippet.description: Following similar protests in San Francisco and Oakland, demonstrators blocked tech shuttle buses in the Great Northwest.

snippet.title: Seidio Innotraveler Universal Car Mount
snippet.description: The Seidio Innotraveler's hinged structure proved difficult to adjust, and its screws were prone to come loose in our testing.
